    <section>
        <h1>References and Research</h1>
        <p>A huge thanks to all those developer websites (<a href="https://css-tricks.com/" rel="nofollow">CSS-Tricks</a>, <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/" rel="nofollow">Stack Overflow</a>, and <a href="http://www.w3schools.com/" rel="nofollow">W3Schools</a> to name a few) and their communities. I would not have been able to get this far without them, as they offer very good advice and tips for overcoming design obstacles.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h1>Queries or Complaints</h1>
        <p>If you have a problem with any of the content on this site, or if you would like to report a bug or error, please don't hesitate to @Html.ActionLink("contact me", "contact", "about").</p>
        <p>If you like the design, and would be interested in having a website created for you, I would be more than willing to help you. @Html.ActionLink("Get in touch", "contact", "about") with me, and we can discuss the details.</p>
    </section>
</div>